SY - Send a system message

Syntax:   SY=<message>
Response: SY/<system response>

Settable parameters:
<message>: the message to be sent to the system. MESSS is called
           and the <message> sent directly. The response, if any,
           is displayed and logged.

      Comments: The message may contain any of CI's base set
commands, which are those allowed from the system prompt. Base set
commands are those CI commands indicated with an asterisk(*) in
the RTE-A User's manual and Quick Reference Guide.
